<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="SimpleMauiApp._5section">
    <ScrollView>
        <VerticalStackLayout>
            <!-- Chapter Title -->
            <Label 
                Text="Functions of an Operating System"
                FontSize="24"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                HorizontalOptions="Center"
                Margin="10" />

            <!-- Introduction -->
            <Label 
                Text="An Operating System (OS) is a complex system designed to manage hardware and software resources efficiently. Below is an in-depth look at the key functions performed by an OS:"
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10" 
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Center" />

            <!-- Resource Management -->
            <Label 
                Text="1. Resource Management"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="The OS manages resources such as CPU, memory, storage, and I/O devices. It ensures resources are allocated effectively among various processes, preventing conflicts and maximizing efficiency."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: Task scheduling and memory allocation in multi-user systems."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- Process Management -->
            <Label 
                Text="2. Process Management"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="Processes are instances of running programs. The OS handles their creation, scheduling, synchronization, and termination. It also resolves conflicts between processes by managing their priorities."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: Managing background tasks and foreground applications in Windows."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- Memory Management -->
            <Label 
                Text="3. Memory Management"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="Memory management involves tracking each memory location, allocating memory to processes, and reclaiming memory from terminated processes. The OS also uses techniques like paging and segmentation for efficient memory usage."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: Virtual memory systems in modern OSs like Windows and Linux."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- File System Management -->
            <Label 
                Text="4. File System Management"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="The OS organizes, stores, retrieves, and manages data on storage devices. It handles file naming, permissions, and operations like reading and writing."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: NTFS (Windows) and ext4 (Linux) file systems."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- Security and Access Control -->
            <Label 
                Text="5. Security and Access Control"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="The OS ensures system security by implementing user authentication, access permissions, and encryption. It prevents unauthorized access and safeguards sensitive data."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: Secure boot and data encryption features in modern OSs."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- Device Management -->
            <Label 
                Text="6. Device Management"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="The OS coordinates input and output operations, managing communication between devices and software. It uses device drivers to abstract hardware complexity for applications."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: Plug-and-play device handling in Windows."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- User Interface -->
            <Label 
                Text="7. User Interface Management"
                FontSize="18"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                Margin="10" />
            <Label 
                Text="The OS provides a user-friendly interface, either graphical (GUI) or command-line (CLI), to allow users to interact with the system and perform tasks efficiently."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />
            <Label 
                Text="Example: Windows Explorer and Linux terminal."
                FontSize="14"
                Margin="10"
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Start" />

            <!-- Summary -->
            <Label 
                Text="Each function of the Operating System plays a vital role in ensuring seamless interaction between users, applications, and hardware resources. A deeper understanding of these functions reveals the sophistication of modern computing environments."
                FontSize="16"
                Margin="10" 
                HorizontalTextAlignment="Center" />

            <!-- Next Button -->
            <Button
                Text="Continue"
                BackgroundColor="Blue"
                TextColor="White"
                FontAttributes="Bold"
                HorizontalOptions="Center"
                VerticalOptions="End"
                Margin="10"
                Clicked="NextClicked" />
        </VerticalStackLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</ContentPage>